some notes from the hangout last night

‚Ä¢ The Marketplace of Trust (MoT) mechanic allows users to gain trust by providing trading recommendations to the AI agent, including ticker symbol, buy/sell action, conviction level, and reasoning, without requiring them to actually buy or sell tokens. It operates in a "virtual marketplace".

‚Ä¢ User trust scores range from -1 to 1, starting at 0 for new users. Scores are primarily based on the historical performance of their recommendations, with initial scores slightly influenced by token holdings (20-30% max).

‚Ä¢ The AI agent incorporates user recommendations into its decision-making process but ultimately makes autonomous trades based on market data, token analysis, and aggregated community sentiment to prevent gaming. Users have no guarantee the agent will follow their specific advice.

‚Ä¢ If the community identifies a scam/bad faith recommendation, trusted members can coordinate a "rage sell" to quickly dump the token or burn the tokens to avoid negatively impacting well-intentioned communities.

‚Ä¢ A 2-week window will be used to gather initial recommendation data and build trust scores before the agent starts actual trading.

‚Ä¢ The amount of trust gained or lost per recommendation is capped to prevent excessive influence from a single call. Users can also gain trust by accurately identifying scams or warning against bad trades.

‚Ä¢ High-trust users have more influence on the AI agent's decisions, but no single user has absolute control.

‚Ä¢ Leaderboards showing user trust rankings were considered but deemed too gameable at this stage. The focus is on gathering quality data from a smaller trusted user set first.

‚Ä¢ The initial version of AI Marc will be invite-only in a private Discord. Public Twitter presence will come later once it can publish sound investment theses.

‚Ä¢ The MoT aims to create an engaging, community-driven investing experience where users are incentivized to provide high-quality, well-reasoned trading recommendations, resistant to common forms of gaming or manipulation.

‚Ä¢ Work being done to clean up the code base and improve documentation for those using Eliza framework.
